From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A CI <ci@vyos-ls1046a>
Date: Fri, 30 May 2026 04:26:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa/af_xdp_pool: add dormant true-ZC RX Recover sw-ring
 reverse-map (M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 4a, infrastructure, no datapath
 consumer)

M3-3 step 7 (true zero-copy RX, spec sec 6.1.7) couples two inseparable
write-side mechanisms that must land together (sub-increment 4b / patch
0103b): the reProgram WRITE -- fman_port_set_rx_bpool() from patch 0102 --
that points the live FMan RX port at the dedicated XSK BMan pool, and the
Recover redirect that turns each XSK-pool-sourced FD into an
xdp_do_redirect() into the AF_XDP socket. Firing the reProgram WITHOUT a
working Recover is a guaranteed crash (spec sec 6.1.8 class: list_add
free-list corruption in xp_alloc(), dcache_clean_poc paging fault, 52 s
soft-lockup) because FMan would DMA into XSK chunks that the build_skb()
skbuf path then consumes as page-pool pages.

The Recover redirect needs to turn a BMan-returned chunk DMA cookie
(qm_fd_addr(fd), the only datum available at rx_default_dqrr) back into the
originating struct xdp_buff *. The spec sec 6.1.15 prose named
xsk_buff_recv() as the API for this -- but an API survey of kernel 6.18.31
confirms NO such primitive exists (`grep -rn xsk_buff_recv include/net/
include/net/xdp/` = zero hits). The present xsk_buff_* surface is
xsk_buff_alloc / xsk_buff_alloc_batch / xsk_buff_set_size /
xsk_buff_dma_sync_for_cpu / xsk_buff_xdp_get_dma / xsk_buff_free /
xsk_pool_dma_map -- there is no retrieve-by-dma call. This is the same
class of gap as the earlier 0075b xsk_pool_get_nentries() non-existence
finding (spec sec 6.1.16).

Mainline ZC drivers (i40e/ice/mlx5) sidestep this by keeping a per-RX-ring
software array of the xsk_buff_alloc() handles indexed by descriptor, and
retrieving the handle at RX. DPAA1's FILL -> BMan-release path
(af_xdp_pool_main.c) currently calls xsk_buff_alloc_batch() then IMMEDIATELY
extracts xsk_buff_xdp_get_dma(handle) and bman_release()es the raw DMA
address -- the xdp_buff * handle is DISCARDED. There is no way to recover
it at RX without first preserving it.

This patch (0103a) builds that missing infrastructure -- and ONLY the
infrastructure -- so the hardware-risky coupled write (0103b) becomes a
small, reviewable, single-purpose follow-up:

  * struct dpaa_priv gains xsk_chunk_map[DPAA1_XSK_MAX_QBANDS] (a per-qband
    flat array of struct xdp_buff * keyed by UMEM chunk index, O(1) lookup,
    no hash collisions) and xsk_chunk_map_len[] (allocated slot count;
    0 = dormant).

  * Two static helpers, dpaa_xsk_chunk_record() and dpaa_xsk_chunk_lookup(),
    perform the record (chunk_idx -> xdp_buff) and lookup with bounds and
    NULL-map guards. _lookup() bumps a new diagnostic counter
    xsk_zc_recover_lookup (21st xsk_* line) on a successful resolve.

  * attach allocates the map (kcalloc, non-fatal on failure -- the map
    stays NULL and both helpers early-return, leaving the datapath on the
    unchanged skbuf path, exactly 0102); detach frees it.

  * A one-shot self-test in attach records a stack sentinel at slot 0,
    looks it back, asserts equality, and clears it -- proving the
    record/lookup round-trip and exercising both static helpers (so no
    -Wunused-function) WITHOUT touching any hardware or live chunk.

CRITICALLY this patch adds NO datapath caller: the FILL-release path does
NOT yet record into the map, and rx_default_dqrr does NOT yet consult it.
The reProgram WRITE stays unfired. Per the dormant-primitive cadence used
for every prior offload primitive (fman_hm_node_install 0090,
fman_policer_install 0091, fman_port_set_rx_bpool 0102), the running kernel
is byte-identical to the 0102 build on every flavor -- the only observable
change is xsk_zc_recover_lookup ticking up by a small fixed amount per
XDP_ZEROCOPY attach (the self-test), never growing with traffic until
0103b lands.

The 21st xsk_* ethtool counter is surfaced by extending the SEPARATE
string table dpaa_stats_xsk[] in dpaa_ethtool.c (the value-collection
loop is already ARRAY_SIZE(dpaa_stats_xsk)-driven and memcpy's the
contiguous u64 block at &priv->xsk_pool_attach_ok, so the new
xsk_zc_recover_lookup field -- placed immediately after
xsk_zc_rx_recovered in dpaa_eth.h, the 21st contiguous u64 -- maps
1:1 to the new string). Without this the field exists and is bumped
but ethtool -S never lists it (the get-strings/get-stats walk stops at
the 20-entry table). dpaa_get_sset_count() already adds
DPAA_STATS_XSK_LEN so the count stays consistent.

Native cross-compile verified: af_xdp_pool_main.o (CC [M]) and dpaa_eth.o
both build clean with LOCALVERSION=-vyos, zero warnings, no
-Wunused-function on the new static helpers.

Spec: specs/dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md sec 6.1.15 (corrected),
sec 6.1.16 (API gap), sub-increment 4a.
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
index dcb69be..0a5fa49 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
@@ -26,6 +26,7 @@
 #include <linux/init.h>
 #include <linux/kernel.h>
 #include <linux/module.h>
+#include <linux/slab.h>
 #include <linux/types.h>
 #include <linux/errno.h>
 #include <linux/printk.h>
@@ -111,6 +112,40 @@ return false;
  *   patch 0075b because it requires xsk_buff_alloc_batch() which only
  *   makes sense once we own the pool (post-attach).
  */
+/*
+ * dpaa_xsk_chunk_record / dpaa_xsk_chunk_lookup (patch 0103a)
+ *
+ * DORMANT Recover sw-ring reverse-map helpers.  0103b will call
+ * _record() at FILL-release time (preserving the xdp_buff handle that
+ * the BMan-release path currently discards) and _lookup() at RX to turn
+ * a chunk DMA cookie back into its xdp_buff for xsk_buff_set_size() +
+ * xsk_buff_dma_sync_for_cpu() + xdp_do_redirect().  Until 0103b these
+ * are exercised ONLY by the one-shot self-test in attach (below); the
+ * datapath never calls them, so behaviour is byte-identical to 0102.
+ */
+static void dpaa_xsk_chunk_record(struct dpaa_priv *priv, u16 band,
+			  u32 chunk_idx, struct xdp_buff *xdp)
+{
+	if (unlikely(!priv->xsk_chunk_map[band] ||
+		     chunk_idx >= priv->xsk_chunk_map_len[band]))
+		return;
+	priv->xsk_chunk_map[band][chunk_idx] = xdp;
+}
+
+static struct xdp_buff *dpaa_xsk_chunk_lookup(struct dpaa_priv *priv,
+				      u16 band, u32 chunk_idx)
+{
+	struct xdp_buff *xdp;
+
+	if (unlikely(!priv->xsk_chunk_map[band] ||
+		     chunk_idx >= priv->xsk_chunk_map_len[band]))
+		return NULL;
+	xdp = priv->xsk_chunk_map[band][chunk_idx];
+	if (xdp)
+		priv->xsk_zc_recover_lookup++;
+	return xdp;
+}
+
 static int af_xdp_pool_xsk_pool_attach(struct dpaa_priv *priv,
        struct xsk_buff_pool *pool,
        u16 queue_id)
@@ -213,6 +248,18 @@ ret = xsk_pool_dma_map(pool, priv->rx_dma_dev,
 	priv->xsk_bpid[queue_id]  = bman_get_bpid(bpool);
 	priv->xsk_bpool[queue_id] = bpool;
 
+	/* 0103a: allocate the DORMANT Recover reverse-map for this qband.
+	 * One xdp_buff* slot per initial-seed chunk.  Failure is non-fatal
+	 * -- the map stays NULL and _record/_lookup early-return, leaving
+	 * the datapath on the unchanged skbuf path (exactly 0102).  Freed
+	 * in detach.
+	 */
+	priv->xsk_chunk_map[queue_id] =
+		kcalloc(DPAA1_XSK_INITIAL_SEED, sizeof(struct xdp_buff *),
+			GFP_KERNEL);
+	priv->xsk_chunk_map_len[queue_id] =
+		priv->xsk_chunk_map[queue_id] ? DPAA1_XSK_INITIAL_SEED : 0;
+
 	/*
 	 * Step 4: Seed the new BMan pool from the XSK fill ring.
 	 *
@@ -351,6 +398,25 @@ dev_info(priv->net_dev->dev.parent,
  priv->dpaa_bp->bpid);
 }
 
+/* 0103a: one-shot DORMANT self-test of the Recover reverse-map.
+ * Record a sentinel xdp_buff pointer at slot 0, look it back, and
+ * clear it -- proving _record/_lookup round-trip and bumping
+ * xsk_zc_recover_lookup exactly once per successful attach.  This
+ * touches NO hardware and NO live chunk; it only writes/reads the
+ * driver-private array.  0103b replaces this self-test with the
+ * real FILL-release record + RX lookup.
+ */
+if (priv->xsk_chunk_map[queue_id]) {
+struct xdp_buff sentinel;
+
+dpaa_xsk_chunk_record(priv, queue_id, 0, &sentinel);
+if (dpaa_xsk_chunk_lookup(priv, queue_id, 0) != &sentinel)
+dev_warn(priv->net_dev->dev.parent,
+ "af_xdp_pool: qband %u Recover reverse-map self-test FAILED\n",
+ queue_id);
+dpaa_xsk_chunk_record(priv, queue_id, 0, NULL);
+}
+
 return 0;
 
 err_unmap:
@@ -535,6 +601,11 @@ bman_free_pool(bpool);
 priv->xsk_bpool[queue_id] = NULL;
 priv->xsk_bpid[queue_id]  = 0;
 
+/* 0103a: free the Recover reverse-map. */
+kfree(priv->xsk_chunk_map[queue_id]);
+priv->xsk_chunk_map[queue_id]     = NULL;
+priv->xsk_chunk_map_len[queue_id] = 0;
+
 /* Step 9: re-enable the FMan RX port for default (non-XSK) FQs. */
 if (rxp) {
 ret = fman_port_enable(rxp);
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
index d9b782f..eef321a 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
@@ -242,6 +242,32 @@ u32 hm_vlan_strip_handle;
 	struct bman_pool           *xsk_bpool[DPAA1_XSK_MAX_QBANDS];
 	unsigned int                xsk_max_qbands;
 
+	/* M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 4a (patch 0103a): true-ZC RX Recover
+	 * sw-ring reverse-map -- DORMANT infrastructure with no datapath
+	 * consumer.  The productive Recover redirect (0103b) needs to turn a
+	 * BMan-returned chunk DMA cookie (qm_fd_addr(fd)) back into the
+	 * originating struct xdp_buff *, but kernel 6.18.31 has no
+	 * xsk_buff_recv()/retrieve-by-dma primitive (the spec sec 6.1.15
+	 * prose named an API that does not exist -- see sec 6.1.16).  Mainline
+	 * ZC drivers (i40e/ice/mlx5) keep a per-RX-ring sw array of the
+	 * xsk_buff_alloc() handles indexed by descriptor; DPAA1's FILL ->
+	 * BMan-release path discards the handle after xsk_buff_xdp_get_dma().
+	 * This array restores that mapping: at FILL-release time 0103b will
+	 * record (chunk_dma -> xdp_buff) here; at RX it will look the cookie
+	 * up.  Allocated/seeded/freed in attach/detach (0103a), but NEITHER
+	 * recorded into NOR consulted by the datapath until 0103b flips the
+	 * reprogram WRITE + redirect on -- so the running kernel is
+	 * byte-identical to the 0102 build on every flavor.
+	 *
+	 * Indexed by qband; each entry is a flat array of
+	 * DPAA1_XSK_INITIAL_SEED struct xdp_buff * slots keyed by UMEM chunk
+	 * index, giving O(1) lookup with no hash collisions.
+	 * xsk_chunk_map_len records the slot count actually allocated
+	 * (0 = dormant/unallocated).
+	 */
+	struct xdp_buff           **xsk_chunk_map[DPAA1_XSK_MAX_QBANDS];
+	u32                         xsk_chunk_map_len[DPAA1_XSK_MAX_QBANDS];
+
 	/* AF_XDP zerocopy ethtool / debugfs counters. Bumped by the
 	 * flavor module's attach/detach/NAPI paths. Phase 2 introduces
 	 * attach/detach/seed/dma/align/headroom/mtu/pamu counters;
@@ -364,6 +390,18 @@ u64 xsk_fill_guard_block;
  */
 u64 xsk_zc_rx_recovered;
 
+/* M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 4a (patch 0103a): Recover sw-ring
+ * reverse-map diagnostic.  Bumped by dpaa_xsk_chunk_lookup() when a
+ * chunk DMA cookie is successfully resolved back to its xdp_buff.
+ * DORMANT: the lookup helper is exercised by a one-shot self-test at
+ * attach time (record N, look the same N back, free), but the RX
+ * hot-path does NOT call it until 0103b.  Increments exactly once
+ * per successful attach (the self-test) -- 0 until the first
+ * XDP_ZEROCOPY bind, then a small fixed number, never growing with
+ * traffic until 0103b.  21st xsk_* line.
+ */
+u64 xsk_zc_recover_lookup;
+
 /* M3-3b (patch 0086): FMan PCD capability bitmask snapshot taken
  * at probe via dpaa_fman_get_caps(). 0 on mainline ucode 106 ->
  * all fman_cc_tree_/fman_hm_/fman_pol_ helpers short-circuit
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_ethtool.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_ethtool.c
index dbc3720..4ac4583 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_ethtool.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_ethtool.c
@@ -75,6 +75,7 @@ static char dpaa_stats_xsk[][ETH_GSTRING_LEN] = {
 "xsk_zc_rx_armed",
 "xsk_fill_guard_block",
 "xsk_zc_rx_recovered",
+"xsk_zc_recover_lookup",
 };
 
 /* HW-offload (PCD-cap) counters (M3-3b / patch 0086). Order MUST match

